\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
MultiGWAS: A tool for GWAS analysis on tetraploid organisms by integrating
 four GWAS software
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\series bold
Summary:
\series default
 The Genome-Wide Association Studies (GWAS) are essential to determine the
 association between genetic variants across individuals.
 One way to support the results is by using different tools to validate
 the reproducibility of the associations.
 Currently, software for GWAS in diploids is well-established but for polyploids
 species is scarce.
 Each GWAS software has its characteristics, which can cost time and effort
 to use them successfully.
 Here, we present MultiGWAS, a tool 
\change_deleted -1666014648 1589332260
to do
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589332263
 perform
\change_unchanged
 GWAS analysis in tetraploid organisms by executing in parallel and integrating
 the results from four existing GWAS 
\change_deleted -1666014648 1589332369
software
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589332372
 packages
\change_unchanged
: two available for polyploids (GWASpoly and SHEsis) and two frequently
 used for diploids (PLINK and TASSEL).
 The tool deals with all the elements of the GWAS process in the four 
\change_deleted -1666014648 1589332498
software
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589332501
packages
\change_unchanged
, including 
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589337295
(1) Genomica data management from different input formats 
\change_unchanged
(
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589333604
2
\change_deleted -1666014648 1589333603
1
\change_unchanged
) 
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589333660
Data cleaning using 
\change_deleted -1666014648 1589333773
the use of 
\change_unchanged
different control quality filters
\change_deleted -1666014648 1589333781
 for the genomic data
\change_unchanged
, 
\change_inserted -1666014648 1589337387
