\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
\color blue
Main view of the MultiGWAS graphical user interface.

\series default
 The interface shows a main view on the center, a toolbar on the left and
 four tabs on top.
 From the main view, users can specify the input parameters for the analysis.
 From the toolbar, users can select the GWAS packages to be used in the
 analysis (two for tetraploids and two for diploids), and start the analysis
 with the current parameters (or load a previously saved configuration).
 And, from the tabs, in addition to specifying the input parameters, users
 can view the outputs of the process, the results of the analysis as an
 html report, and browse the source files that support the report.
