\begin_layout Section
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%PAULA: Falta discutir un tris los resultados a nivel de información
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%PAULA: Tools diploides vs Tools poliploides en poliploides - dosis de los
 alelos
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%Paula Consideraciones para polyploides que afectan multiGWAS requieren
 estudios
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%polyploides allele frequencies (alllele copy number).
 A way to solve is considering that each allele in partial heterozygotes
 has an equal likekihood of being present in more tahn one copy
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

% HW polyploides autopolyploides tengo dudas si se cumple - porque la segregació
n es diferente
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Challenges studying polyploid organisms are related to the complexity of
 (1) the data, and (2) inheritance mechanisms that are under study (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "dufresne2014"

\end_inset

).
 The difficulties regarding the data complexity are the uncertainty in the
 allele dosage and null alleles, but these problems are opportunities to
 improve software at the variant calling stage.
 Moreover, there is an on-going understanding of the inheritance mechanisms
 for polyploids.
 For autopolyploids, most loci have a polysomic inheritance.
 However, sections of the genome that did not duplicate lead to disomic
 inheritance for some loci (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ohno1970,lynch2000,dufresne2014"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
MultiGWAS does not face the problem of the allele dosage uncertainty.
 It is necessary to measure the impact of the allele dosage uncertainty
 at the GWAS stage to understand the effects arisen from this problem at
 the association stage.
 However, MultiGWAS addresses the second challenge variation of inheritance
 mechanisms by using different for existing software: two designed for polysomic
 inheritance (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Rosyara2016,Shen2016"

\end_inset

) together with two for disomic inheritance (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Purcell2007,Bradbury2007"

\end_inset

).
 Thus it is a useful tool for researchers because it looks for significative
 associations that involve both types of inheritance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%selección del modelo adecuado para cada tool - %Paula: Para polyploides
 el modo de inheritance es complejo por eso una selección del tool basada
 en replicabilidad y el factor de inflación es una propuesta justificada
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pr
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

{
\end_layout

\end_inset

Luis esta parte revisala por fa.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Moreover, GWASpoly (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Rosyara2016"

\end_inset

) offers models for different types of polyploid gene action additive, diploidiz
ed additive, duplex dominant, simplex dominant, and general.
 On the other hand, TASSEL (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Bradbury2007"

\end_inset

) also models different types of gene action for diploids general, additive
 and dominant.
 We propose an automatic selection of the gene action model for both tools
 based on a balance between the factor of inflation and the replicability
 of the identified SNPs.
 We inform the user of the selected model based on the automatic strategy;
 we consider this information helps to understand the gene action model
 for the trait of interest.
 Even though the main focus is on the resultant SNPs, the model has assumptions
 that reflect the gene actions for a specific phenotype.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%PAULA: ventaja de integrar - pvalores inflados de shesis  (Balance entre
 sensitividad y especificidad al integrar)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset

Replicability is a strategy to assess results derived from different methods.
 MultiGWAS integrates results to check for replicability in the results
 from different software.
 By combining results, we can compare the outputs and look for coincidences.
 Some software are more sensible, and others are more specific, but the
 integration allows MultiGWAS to balance specificity and sensitivity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We provide the user with different graphic outputs to help to interpret
 the results.
 We report the SNP profile for the SNPs identified by more than one software.
 The SNP profile gives the researcher visual feedback from the SNP.
 We previously check for significative SNPs based on the p-value; however,
 it is essential to go back to the data and check if the SNP is a real associati
on between the genotype and phenotype.
 For this purpose, we designed the SNP profile.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
For GWAS packages using several gene action models (e.g.
 GWASpoly and TASSEL), MultiGWAS automatically selects one of them to perform
 the integration with the others GWAS packages.
 This selection takes into account two parameters: the replicability and
 the inflation factor of each gene action model as at it was shown using
 different action model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Muchos de los rasgos de interés en las plantas están asociados tanto a múltiples
 genes, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Cuando las herramientas diploides y tetraploides en conjunto asocian un
 mismo marcador al rasgo de interés entonces esa asociación necesitó solo
 de la información diploide.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset bibtex
LatexCommand bibtex
bibfiles "multiGWAS"
options "plain"

\end_inset


\end_layout

